OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FLord Geidt: PM's ex-ethics 
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fadviser reveals more about 
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5Fwhy he quit                
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, Boris Johnson's former ethics adviser  
OL,6, has said he resigned from his role this
OL,7, week over the government's "openness"  
OL,8, to breaking international law.         
OL,10,FIn a second letter outlining why he had
OL,11,Fquit, Lord Geidt said reports it was   
OL,12,Frelated to steel tariffs were a        
OL,13,F"distraction".                         
OL,15,F"I could not be a party to advising on 
OL,16,Fany potential law-breaking," he said.  
OL,18,FLord Geidt was the second ethics       
OL,19,Fadviser to quit under Mr Johnson, after
OL,20,FSir Alex Allan left in 2020.           
